{
  "stem": "1282.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They still believed that on Easter, we kill a child and drink the child's blood to the point where many Jewish people on Easter didn't even show their-- didn't get out of the house.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They believed in the blood sacrifice, you know, the blood libel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Therefore, as little children not understanding what they are talking about knew that a Jew is to be hated.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He killed our Lord.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, when you attend public school, and at that time, religion was-- in this country, we have separation of religion from, from, from government--",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--yeah, religion from state.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not the case there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For example, twice a month, the priest came and taught the Gentile kids the religion, the Gentile religion.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, we have had the privilege of stepping out of that room, and we went to cheder for those few hours.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we did not sit in the classroom or get classroom time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So immediately, Jews stepped out because no one would sit in and listen to the priest.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was an awesome feeling because name-calling, you know, stone-throwing from the little kids and--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[UKRAINIAN] go back to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You don't belong here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, you know, you felt it every moment in every day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You were-- you were needed, but not necessarily loved.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I cannot do it properly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But [UKRAINIAN] is Jew in Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You belong to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Go to Jerusalem.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't even know what Palestine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't know what Jerusalem meant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They heard it from their parents.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Kids repeated it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was the feeling that existed in most homes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was no love for the Jew at all.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Jew was needed because the Jew was the carpenter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The Jew was the shoemaker.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Jew was a tradesman.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Jew had the store.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
